    <p class="text-xl text-gray-600 mb-12 max-w-3xl">Sri Lankan food is one of Asia's great undiscovered cuisines — bold, fragrant, deeply spiced, and extraordinarily varied. From the humble rice and curry eaten three times a day to the crispy street-food pleasure of kottu roti at midnight, eating your way across the island is one of its greatest pleasures.</p>

